On Sun, 7 Oct 2007, Phil Trenholme wrote:

> Possibly the chance of damaging the aluminum head as a result of trying to
> fit a misaligned bolt or from repeated removal and replacement of a steel
> bolt into an aluminum casting? Phil

>  Anyone care to conjecture as to why the Type IV engine has studs on the
>  intake and exhaust to the heads, rather than bolts?

Also, properly cut threads for studs are slightly tighter than those for
bolts.  Studs should not be able to be turned into their holes by fingers.

